Reasoning: The paper presents a framework for learning with relational spatio-temporal features in the processing and interpretation of dynamic visuo-spatial imagery. This involves the use of logic and cognition, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of visuo-spatial language and imagery suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the application in the domain of computing for visual arts and computational cognitive science suggests a possible focus on computer graphics (cs.CC).
